---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Celtic Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score"
  description="Celtic mythology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. DRUID 7pts, BARD 7pts, FAERY 11pts, WYVERN 15pts. Celtic vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble celtic mythology words, druid scrabble points, bard scrabble, faery scrabble word, celtic scrabble terms, wyvern scrabble, mythology words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Celtic Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score","description":"Celtic mythology words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. DRUID 7pts, BARD 7pts, FAERY 11pts, WYVERN 15pts.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-celtic"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is FAERY a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! FAERY scores 11 points (F=4, A=1, E=1, R=1, Y=4). It's an archaic spelling of fairy, associated with the Celtic otherworld. Both the F tile (4pts) and Y tile (4pts) contribute strong value to this 5-letter word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is DRUID worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"DRUID scores 7 points (D=2, R=1, U=1, I=1, D=2). A Celtic priest or magician of ancient Gaul and Britain. The two D tiles (2pts each) provide the bulk of the scoring."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BARD valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. BARD scores 7 points (B=3, A=1, R=1, D=2) and means a Celtic poet or storyteller. The B tile (3pts) and D tile (2pts) make this short 4-letter word surprisingly efficient at 1.75 points per tile."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Celtic Mythology — Ancient Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Celtic mythology brings mystical words to your Scrabble rack. Terms like DRUID, BARD, and FAERY have crossed from ancient legend into the dictionary — and they score surprisingly well. The F and Y tiles in FAERY, the W in WYVERN — these mythological words put premium consonants to work.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">15 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">WYVERN (Top)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">11 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FAERY</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DRUID</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">7 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BARD</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Celtic Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">WYVERN — 15 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">W=4, Y=4, V=4, E=1, R=1, N=1 · 6 letters · Triple-4 combo</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">A two-legged dragon from Celtic and heraldic tradition. WYVERN stacks three 4-point tiles (W, Y, V) with three 1-point tiles. At 15 points from 6 letters (2.5 per tile), it's an exceptional way to clear premium consonants from your rack.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧚 FAERY</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · F=4, A=1, E=1, R=1, Y=4 · Celtic otherworld spirit</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🌳 DRUID</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · D=2, R=1, U=1, I=1, D=2 · Celtic priest-magician</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🎵 BARD</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">7 pts · B=3, A=1, R=1, D=2 · Celtic poet-singer</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⚔️ GLYPH</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">14 pts · G=2, L=1, Y=4, P=3, H=4 · Carved symbol</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Mythological Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">RUNE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TORC</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OGHAM</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PIXIE</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">14pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ELFIN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">8pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COVEN</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Mythology Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FAERY clears F and Y together:</span> Both F (4pts) and Y (4pts) are awkward tiles that sit on racks too long. FAERY dumps both in one play while scoring 11 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">DRUID pluralises to DRUIDS:</span> At 8 points, DRUIDS adds an S for minimal cost. Play DRUID first, then hook the S on your next turn if the lane stays open.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BARD is a 4-letter gem:</span> At 7 points from 4 tiles (1.75/tile), BARD outscores most 4-letter words. It also extends to BARDS and BARDIC for bonus plays.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Celtic mythology words specialise in <span class="text-white font-medium">clearing awkward consonants</span> — W, V, Y, and F all appear frequently. WYVERN alone uses three 4-point tiles in one word. Keep these words ready when your rack fills with mid-value consonants.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-mythology-japanese/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Mythology Japanese</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-fencing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Fencing</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gemstones/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gemstones</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid mythology word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
